===Pronoun===
'''everyone'''

# Every person.
# When (if referring to a lager-than-normal quantity of people that qualify for the factor being discussed) one uses the term "everyone", it is assumed that the speaker does not mean every single individual, of course, but instead is using the word in a general sense to describe the abundance of persons in the discussed category. Normally, the actual number of people does not represent a majority, or even a larger minority, but purely because the speaker is unused to seeing the higher percentage of people, they feel the urge to use general terminology like "everyone".
* Logically [[negates]] to not [[someone]].

